#: 21337012-0-3225
msgctxt "21337012-0-3225"
msgid ""
"A Discourse on Faith by Ugdorga, the King's Scribe\n"
"\n"
"For generations, Orcs have believed in three constant truths: the "
"stronghold, the grudge, and the fury of Malacath. But before Malacath, at "
"least according to certain traditions and a few noted scholars, there was "
"Trinimac. Today, the city of Orsinium reverberates with the intellectual "
"debate and reverent faith of both sides of the argument: Who is the true god "
"of the Orcs?\n"
"\n"
"For traditionalists, there is no question. Malacath is lord and god. He "
"personifies the Sworn Oath and the Bloody Curse. His portfolio includes "
"conflict, battle, broken promises, and anguish. Everything an Orc feels "
"concerning his or her place in the world comes from the Furious One. The "
"Orcs see themselves as a people betrayed, and Malacath reinforces this "
"belief. For Malacath, clans must stand powerful but alone in their ancestral "
"strongholds. The strongest rules and weakness is cast out with extreme "
"intolerance.\n"
"\n"
"Clan chiefs such as Chief Bazrag, who oppose the idea of an Orsimer king, "
"hold to the teachings of Malacath.\n"
"\n"
"For the new Orsimer, Trinimac is the culmination of their dreams and desires."
" The warrior god personifies culture and civilization. He calls for unity, "
"not discord; for strength, not malicious chaos. He stands for unifying the "
"Orsimer. For elevating us above our baser nature and making us equal to the "
"other races.\n"
"\n"
"King Kurog and the Orsimer of Orsinium follow the teachings of Trinimac."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-3225
msgctxt "51188213-0-3225"
msgid "Malacath and Trinimac"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-3224
msgctxt "21337012-0-3224"
msgid ""
"<<1>>,\n"
"\n"
"Accept this invitation, carried by one of my most-trusted messengers, in "
"friendship and respect. In the name of the mighty King Kurog, I bid you "
"welcome and invite you to test your mettle in the wilds of majestic Wrothgar."
"\n"
"\n"
"The Orsimer care not where your loyalties lie. Come help us rebuild the city "
"of Orsinium and squelch the Winterborn menace. Aid the king in his worthy "
"endeavors and riches and honors will be bestowed upon you.\n"
"\n"
"I have sent Ambassador Lazgara to meet you and offer you transportation to "
"Wrothgar. You can find her in one of the following cities: Daggerfall, "
"Davon's Watch, or Vulkhel Guard. Look for her when you arrive.\n"
"\n"
"I look forward to meeting you in person, as I've heard such wonderful "
"accounts of your adventures. Present yourself to me when you arrive in "
"Orsinium.\n"
"\n"
"Forge-Mother Alga,\n"
"Orsinium, Wrothgar"
msgstr ""
"<<1>>,\n"
"\n"
"내가 가장 신뢰하는 사신들 중 한명을 통해 이 우정과 존경을 담긴 초대장을 전달하니, 초대를 받아주었으면 하네. 위대한 쿠로그 왕의 "
"이름으로, 그대들을 환영하네 그리고 장엄한 로스가의 황야에서 그대들의 기개를 시험해 보고 싶네.\n"
"\n"
"오시머는 그대들이 어느 진영에 충성하는지는 신경쓰지 않네. 오시니움의 도시를 재건하는데 도움을 주고 윈터본의 위협을 진압하는데 "
"협력해주었으면 하네. 그대들이 왕을 돕는다면 부와 명예를 그대들의 것이네.\n"
"\n"
"그대들을 로스가로 맞이하기 위해 교통편과 라즈가라 대사를 그대에게 보내네. 그대는 그녀를 대거폴과, 다본의 감시탑 , 그리고 벌켈 "
"가드에서 볼 수 있을걸세. 그곳에 도착한다면 그녀를 찾게.\n"
"\n"
"그대의 모험에 대한 훌륭하고 멋진 보고들을 들었고, 그대를 만나기를 고대하고있네. 오시니움에 도착하면 내 앞에 모습을 나타내주게.\n"
"\n"
"대장간대모 알가,\n"
"오시니움, 로스가"

