#: 21337012-0-3037
msgctxt "21337012-0-3037"
msgid ""
"Keen were her eyes\n"
"Even as the doom closed in\n"
"She drew her companions near\n"
"And led the way to glory."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-3037
msgctxt "51188213-0-3037"
msgid "Lakora of the Hunt"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-3036
msgctxt "21337012-0-3036"
msgid ""
"Standing in defiance\n"
"Death would not find his friends\n"
"But would break against his mighty shield\n"
"Ever at their backs."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-3036
msgctxt "51188213-0-3036"
msgid "Baloth Bloodtusk"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-3035
msgctxt "21337012-0-3035"
msgid ""
"Bathing the caverns in light\n"
"Steadfastly he stood between them\n"
"His words of warmth and courage\n"
"Never far from ear."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-3035
msgctxt "51188213-0-3035"
msgid "Mazghar Many-Tongues"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-3032
msgctxt "21337012-0-3032"
msgid ""
"Something controls those strange creatures, surely as it commands the Dwemer "
"constructs. But how, and to what end?\n"
"\n"
"It must have something to do with the pressure valves. Bazorgbeg found "
"three, scattered throughout the ruins—\"\"inceptive, transductive, and "
"astrictive,\"\" he called them. All that heat, all that power, flowing to a "
"locked central chamber. For what purpose? Certainly nothing good.\n"
"\n"
"The pressure valves are key. We must close them immediately! With their "
"pressure released and power diverted, the door to the central chamber should "
"open. I only hope we aren't too—"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-3032
msgctxt "51188213-0-3032"
msgid "Dorand's Final Notes"
msgstr "Dorand의 마지막 쪽지"

#: 21337012-0-2837
msgctxt "21337012-0-2837"
msgid ""
"In the time before song the clans grew restless and clashed steel against "
"steel in the bitter north, until a crimson path was traced in the snow, "
"leading to the mountains of dead and their cairns.\n"
"\n"
"Come autumn the clans called a truce so they might gather the bodies from "
"pasture, range, and farm. So great was the number of dead that the clans saw "
"autumn's return twice over before all the bodies had been gathered.\n"
"\n"
"When they saw the number of the dead, and the fields that lay fallow with "
"none to work them, the chiefs of clans Shar and Tuul met in secret. They "
"said \"\"There is neither glory nor honor in the slaughter of our warriors. "
"The hero that rises this season will die the next and when we are old and "
"grey, will there be any strong Orc left to replace us?\"\"\n"
"\n"
"So they called on Malacath and made an offering of echatere and of their own "
"blood. And the Prince answered them: \n"
"\n"
"\"\"Erect a monument of the dead to me, a cairn for the fallen of clans Shar "
"and Tuul. There pick from among your number the strongest. The contenders "
"will duel atop the cairn until it is consecrated with the blood of the loser."
" The victor shall be chief of a new clan, Shar-tuul.\"\"\n"
"\n"
"The chiefs did as Malacath commanded. The war between the clans ended and a "
"new clan was founded. The place of the first duel was called the Bloody "
"Knoll, for it was built from the bodies of the war-slain and consecrated "
"with the blood of the losing duelist."
msgstr ""

